# Orbit Wars

Python 3.12 RL project (Hydra + JAX PPO). Dependencies: **uv** only (`uv sync --group dev`).

## Commands

- Train: `uv run ow train model=attention training.total_updates=1000`
- Resolved config: `uv run ow train print_resolved_config=true`
- Kaggle: `uv run ow train kaggle`
- Default tests: **`make test`** or **`make test-daily`** (fast ∥ jax, CPU)
- Pre-merge: `make test-premerge` (excludes full sweep); `make test-sweep` before release
- Parallel CPU: `make test-fast-parallel` / `make test-jax-parallel` only — not slow/sweep

## Test policy

- **Never** use `pytest-xdist` or `-n auto` (`tests/conftest.py` blocks it).
- Do **not** run slow/JAX-compile smokes during iteration (`test_jax_rollout`, training-loop smokes, etc.).
- Domain targets: `make test-domain-config`, `test-domain-features`, `test-domain-policy`, `test-domain-artifacts`, `test-domain-curriculum`.
- Check the terminals folder before starting tests if another session may be running pytest.

## Architecture (read before large changes)

- Entry: `src/train.py` → `src/jax/train.py`
- Config: `src/config/schema.py` + `conf/` responsibility groups
- Features: `src/jax/features.py` `encode_turn`; registry in `src/features/`
- Rollout/PPO: `src/jax/rollout/`, `src/jax/ppo_update.py`
- Human priorities: `docs/ROADMAP.md`
- Onboarding: `docs/ONBOARDING.md`, `docs/architecture/`

## Agent workflow

- Use Cursor plugins for planning/review/exploration — see `docs/CURSOR.md`.
- Prefer surgical diffs; run targeted tests after edits (`make test-fast` or `make test-domain-*`).
- Operator docs: `docs/AGENT_CAPABILITIES.md`; session context: `make agent-context`.
- Do not push unless the user asks.
